<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="361" pageId="9" pageNumber="360" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,572,2037]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="361" pageId="9" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1940,1965]" pageId="9" pageNumber="360">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Ismay, 1984" authorityName="Ismay" authorityYear="1984" box="[786,1128,1940,1965]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Dicraeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longisurstylus">
<emphasis box="[786,978,1940,1964]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="360">D. longisurstylus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ismay, J. W." box="[987,1128,1940,1965]" pageId="9" pageNumber="360" pagination="5 - 17" refId="ref12100" refString="Ismay, J. W. (1984) New species of Dicraeus (Diptera: Chloropidae) from New Guinea and New Ireland. Esakia, 21, 5 - 17." type="journal article" year="1984">Ismay, 1984</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be separated from the latter by the following features: ocellar triangle reaching anterior margin of frons; first flagellomere round dorsodistally; scutum with 5 brown to reddish yellow stripes; epandrium with apical and subapical processes on ventral margin. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ismay" authorityYear="1984" box="[363,556,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Dicraeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longisurstylus">
<emphasis box="[363,556,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="361">D. longisurstylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the ocellar triangle reaches anterior 2/3 of frons; the first flagellomere has a dorsodistal angle; the scutum has 3 black stripes, fused basally; and the cercus is narrow and pointed (
<bibRefCitation author="Ismay, J. W." box="[1287,1424,188,212]" pageId="10" pageNumber="361" pagination="5 - 17" refId="ref12100" refString="Ismay, J. W. (1984) New species of Dicraeus (Diptera: Chloropidae) from New Guinea and New Ireland. Esakia, 21, 5 - 17." type="journal article" year="1984">Ismay 1984</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
